2.title: Screen 1
2.content:
During this experiment, you will view a sequence of items appear one at a time on the screen.

Some of these items will be completely NEW items that you have not seen before within the experiment.

Other items will be OLD — items that are identical to those you have previously seen.

Other items will be SIMILAR, but not exactly the same, as items you have previously seen.

Click here and press a key to continue.

rows.title: OrderFiller

7.title: Screen 2
7.content:
As each item appears, you will press a key to indicate if the item is OLD (J), SIMILAR (K), or NEW (L).

Before beginning, we will first show you a few practice items.

Press a key to continue.

rows.title: Set up image

10.title: Screen 3
10.content:
For this item you would say NEW (L), because you have not seen it before in this experiment.

Press a key to continue.

11.title: Screen 4
11.content:
This item is also NEW (L).

Press a key to continue.

14.title: Screen 5
14.content:
This item is NEW (L).

Press a key to continue.

15.title: Screen 6
15.content:
And again, NEW (L).

Press a key to continue.

16.title: Screen 8
16.content:
When this comes up you'd say OLD (J), because it is the same as the one you saw before.

Press a key to continue.

17.title: Screen 9
17.content:
This would be NEW (L).

Press a key to continue.

18.title: Screen 10
18.content:
When this comes up you would say SIMILAR (K),

Press a key to continue...

20.title: Screen 11
20.content:
...because it's similar to one you saw in the experiment, but not the exact same thing.

Press a key to continue.

22.title: Screen 12
22.content:
Here, you'd call this NEW (L).

Press a key to continue.

23.title: Screen 13
23.content:
This one you'd call OLD (J).

Press a key to continue.

24.title: Screen 14
24.content:
This one you'd call similar (K),

Press a key to continue...

25.title: Screen 15
25.content:
...because again, it's similar to one you saw earlier in the experiment, but not the exact same thing.

Press a key to continue.

26.title: Screen 16
26.content:
For each item, you need to indicate if the item is OLD (J), SIMILAR (K), or NEW (L).

You will see cues on the screen to remind you what keys to press for old, similar, and new. When you enter your answer the screen will show what button you pressed, but will not indicate whether you are right or wrong.

Pictures will only stay on the screen for 2 seconds, so try to make your response within that time.

Press a key when you are ready to begin.
